scene.message:
Yukino: You've lost.{waitkey}{clearbox}Your precious prince...{waitkey}{clearbox}no... the "Persona" born{nl}
from your heart{nl}
is gone now.{waitkey}{clearbox}Still want to fight?{waitkey}{clearbox}I don't mind{nl}
either way...{waitkey}{ret}

Kumi: ...In the end...{waitkey}{clearbox}in the end, there's no place{nl}
for me anywhere, is there...{waitkey}{clearbox}Not in reality...{nl}
not in dreams.{waitkey}{clearbox}Aha... I have to run away{nl}
from dreams too...{nl}
ahaha...{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: A person without{nl}
dreams is, by and large,{nl}
shallow and dull.{waitkey}{clearbox}A person who only chases{nl}
dreams is, by and large,{nl}
empty inside.{waitkey}{clearbox}Live without losing your{nl}
dreams, yet without being{nl}
ruled by them.{waitkey}{clearbox}A dream is not something{nl}
merely to chase...{waitkey}{clearbox}nor a place to run to...{waitkey}{clearbox}A dream is nourishment for{nl}
the heart. But a dream you{nl}
only wait for never becomes{waitkey}{clearbox}your own. A dream is not{nl}
given, but something you{nl}
seize with your own{nl}
hands...!{waitkey}Yamaoka often used to say so.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: A grand victory{nl}
by my own might... but...{waitkey}{clearbox}somehow it leaves a{nl}
bad taste...{nl}
This feeling...{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: We did it!{nl}
We won!{waitkey}{clearbox}See that{wait_fr:30}, see that!{nl}
Ayase and friends' skill!{nl}
How's that{wait_fr:30}, how's that!{waitkey}Had enough?!{waitkey}{ret}

Kumi: You're all really{nl}
such strong people...{nl}
If I'd had even a little...{waitkey}of that strength...{waitkey}{clearbox}maybe I could have lived{nl}
without giving in to the{nl}
"Snow Queen's mask"...{waitkey}{clearbox}All I did was blame others,{nl}
keep myself in the safety{nl}
zone, and grumble resentments.{waitkey}{clearbox}I was... just the same as the{nl}
others who blamed me...{nl}
wasn't I.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Hmph...{nl}
Just understanding that{nl}
is good enough.{waitkey}Reflect deeply on it.{waitkey}{clearbox}A dream is indeed nourishment{nl}
for the heart... but fleeing{nl}
into dreams won't{nl}
change reality.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Kumi, having realized{nl}
that, you are no longer{nl}
a weak person.{waitkey}{clearbox}Dreams are like an Oasis{nl}
for our human hearts...{waitkey}{clearbox}quenching the thirst of a{nl}
traveler weary from walking{nl}
the desert of life... yes.{waitkey}{clearbox}But no matter how comfortable{nl}
the Oasis,{waitkey}{clearbox}the traveler must eventually{nl}
set out into the desert{nl}
once more.{waitkey}{clearbox}For however hard it is, so{nl}
long as we live, we humans{nl}
are travelers crossing the{waitkey}desert called "reality"...{waitkey}{ret}

Kumi: Thank you...{nl}
everyone...{waitkey}{clearbox}If only even one friend{nl}
like you had been{nl}
by my side...{waitkey}things might've been better...{waitkey}{clearbox}I won't forget{nl}
any of you...{waitkey}{clearbox}Thank you{wait_fr:30}... farewell.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: "Kumi Hirose"...{waitkey}{clearbox}She wasn't such a{nl}
bad person...{waitkey}{clearbox}She too was a victim whose{nl}
life was twisted{nl}
by the "mask."{waitkey}{clearbox}Now, let's head back!{nl}
We've got to save Ms. Saeko{nl}
quickly!!{waitkey}{ret}
